  "texts": [
    "The analysis of a systems map borrows from graph theory, hence the term graph is used instead of map in this section.",
    "A graph can be characterized at several levels.",
    "At the graph-level, a metric would return a single number, such as the number of nodes.",
    "At the element-level, we produce one number per element (e.g., the number of edges for each node, known as degree) and we either study distributions or focus on the top elements (e.g., most central nodes).",
    "As an intermediate, an analysis can be conducted at the group-level, such as the number of components."
  ],
